  "schema_version": 1.4,
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Catoblepas",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png",
            "name": "Locations",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Catoblepas Nests",
          "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
          "sidebar_type": "locations",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 69",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 69",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 69,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "A catoblepas den is an awful place indeed\u2014a filthy nest composed of piles of decaying vegetation, half-finished or half-digested meals of rotting animals, never-quite-dry banks of mud, and tangles of thorny branches. Worse yet, the catoblepas\u2019s stink infuses such a site, imposing the beast\u2019s ungodly stench upon those who would explore and search it for treasure. A catoblepas nest can retain its stink in this way for up to a week after it\u2019s been abandoned by its foul denizen.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 69",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 69",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 69,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "A catoblepas is an aggressive beast at the best of times. Though it prefers swamps, it has been known to forage in plains and forests for short periods, leaving behind hunting grounds tainted by its foul breath and noxious waste that other predators and prey alike avoid for days or even weeks thereafter. The catoblepas bullies those creatures it believes are a match for it and eats everything weaker.   \n  \nA catoblepas is 15 feet long and weighs 2,200 pounds.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 69",
